               <msContents>
                  <summary>Prayers in Arabic with Turkish commentaries</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Bodl_Or_181-item1" n="1">
                     <title key="">Prayers in Arabic with Turkish commentaries</title>
                     <note>NOTE: This record has been automatically generated with minimal
                        modification from the corresponding entry in a printed catalogue. It
                        may contain errors. Please, consult the References section below for
                        more information.</note>
                     <note>This copy contains in the preliminary part quotations from the
                        Qur'ān, viz. Sūrah 36, on fol. 1b; Sūrah 67, on fol. 15a; Sūrah 78,
                        on fol. 21a; Sūrah 112, on fol. 24b; Sūrah 113, on fol. 25a; Sūrah
                        114, on fol. 25b; Sūrah 1, on fol. 26a; and the beginning of Sūrah
                        2, on fol. 26b. The chief part of the manuscript, ff. 28-80, is
                        filled with various short prayers and talismans, both in Arabic and
                        Turkish, without special headings. Jacobus Tollius received this
                        manuscript 1660, 'ex Illustrissimi Domini D. Nicolai Comitis
                        Serrinii donatione,' and presented it afterwards, 1695, to Henry
                        Chr. de Hennin.</note>
